# CI/CD — GitLab Pipelines

This directory contains GitLab pipeline definitions for validating and deploying your agent project as a Databricks Asset Bundle.

## Pipelines

Pipeline files are under `pipelines/`. The main trigger file is `{{ .input_project_name }}-triggers-cicd.yml`.

| Stage | Trigger | What it does |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| CI | PR to `main` | Validates bundle config, runs unit and integration tests |
| CD (staging) | Merge to `main` | Deploys bundle to staging workspace |
| CD (prod) | Merge to `release` | Deploys bundle to prod workspace |

## Setup

1. Create service principals for staging and prod workspaces
2. Set up GitLab environments (`integration`, `stage`, `production`)
3. Add `SP_CLIENT_ID` and `SP_CLIENT_SECRET` as CI/CD variables scoped to each environment
4. Set the CI/CD configuration file path to `.gitlab/pipelines/{{ .input_project_name }}-triggers-cicd.yml`

## Docker image

Pipelines run on `databricksfieldeng/mlopsstacks:latest` by default. Build a custom image from `docker/` if needed, and update the `image:` line in each pipeline YAML.

For details, see the [AgentOps Setup Guide](../../docs/agentops-setup.md).
